{
  "id": "61e91b3cb3495c001e9ef9f8",
  "title": "(5.2.5.2) Focus on conflict",
  "created": 1555405750,
  "updated": 1555470140,
  "lines": [
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4df",
      "text": "(5.2.5.2) Focus on conflict",
      "created": 1555405750,
      "updated": 1555470140,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e0",
      "text": "To break the existing mental model of \"collecting similar pieces\" or \"grouping based on similarity,\" it is useful to pay attention to the [conflict].",
      "created": 1555405750,
      "updated": 1555405873,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e1",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e2",
      "text": "A participant in a workshop was troubled with group organization. I said to her, \"You can put a conflicting pair in the same group. Because conflict is also a kind of relationship.\"",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405777,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e3",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e4",
      "text": "This advice seems to have destroyed her existing mental model. She got the sense of the KJ method and did the group organization well.",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e5",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e6",
      "text": "---",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405783,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e7",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405783,
      "updated": 1555405783,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e8",
      "text": "[Masakazu Nakayama], author of \"All of the [NM method]\", proposed to focus on \"conflict relations.\"",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405864,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4e9",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405787,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4ea",
      "text": "Suppose you heard the opinions of 20 people in your company on the subject of \"internal company training\" and you have 60 pieces of information.",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4eb",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4ec",
      "text": "Your next action is to find conflict in those pieces. The \"internal company training\" goes a theme of discussion. The fact means that opinions of twenty people are not the same. Then, in those pieces, there must be a pair in conflict. We focus on the conflict.",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4ed",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4ee",
      "text": "After paying attention to the conflict, we make a [hypothesis] that may help resolve the conflict. This way to create a new hypothesis is not a way to organize information, so I explain the details in the next chapter.",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405884,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4ef",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4f0",
      "text": "In the NM method, we focused on the conflict. In the KJ method, we can use any relationship including conflict. ",
      "created": 1555405751,
      "updated": 1555405751,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b3caff09e0000d0b4f1",
      "text": "[en.icon]",
      "created": 1555470140,
      "updated": 1555470140,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    }
  ]
}